<topic xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" base="Princeton" id="Sys_Config_Flash_BadBlock_Download" xml:lang="en-US">
  <title>Flash Bad Block Download (subcommand opcode
  0x06)</title>

  <body>
    <p>Use the Flash Bad Block Download command to download
    the flash bad block entries to the device and add those entries to the
    flash bad block list.</p>

    <fig id="NVM_Express_Vendor_Specific_Command_Flas_5iht97qqbx">
      <title>NVM Express Vendor Specific Command Flash
      Bad Block Download Control Flow</title>

      <image href="Graphics/Admin Command Manager/Flash_BadBlk_Download.svg" placement="break" width="5.5in"/>
    </fig>

    <table id="_5jht97qqbx">
      <title>NVM Express Vendor Specific Command Flash
      Bad Block Download Control Flow</title>

      <tgroup cols="3">
        <colspec colname="c1" colwidth=".5in"/>

        <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1.5in"/>

        <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="4in"/>

        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry>No.</entry>

            <entry>Message</entry>

            <entry>Description</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">1</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CmdReady64</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The command is
            received by one of the Data Managers.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">2</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CmdReady</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Data
            Manager forwards the command to the Admin Command Manager for
            processing.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">3</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">IngressDMA</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Admin
            Command Manager issues ingress DMA requests to transfer the flash
            bad block information to the controller memory.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">4</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">DMACpl</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The DMA engine
            responds with DMA completion messages.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">5</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">FlashBadBlockReq</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Admin
            Command Manager issues requests to the Mapping Manager0 to insert
            entries to flash bad block list.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">6</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">FlashBadBlockCpl</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Mapping
            Manager0 sends the completion to the Admin Command
            Manager.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">7</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CplQueueUpdate</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Admin
            Command Manager sends a completion queue update request to the
            Completion Manager.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">8</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CplQueueUpdateCpl</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Completion
            Manager replies back to the Admin Command Manager when the
            completion has been successfully sent to the host.</p></entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
  </body>
</topic>